                  <p>Greek compound: <i>sun</i> (with) + <i>anti</i> (over against) + <i>lambanō</i> (to take hold of). Literally "takes hold together with, from the opposite side." Not intercession from a distance. Shoulder-to-shoulder labor, carrying the heavy end.</p>
                </div>
