          <!-- LANE INDEX -->
          <article class="s-section" id="components-laneindex">
            <header class="s-section-head">
              <span class="s-section-num">3.10</span>
              <h3>Lane index + filter — <code>.lane-index</code></h3>
            </header>
            <p>A three-cell classification rail. Each cell is a filter trigger — click "Faith" and the archive hides every plate not on that lane. The third cell is the <em>queued</em> state: a lane with no essays yet, rendered dashed and non-interactive. The cell stays visible so the taxonomy is always legible, even when a lane is empty.</p>
            <p class="s-note"><strong>Rules.</strong> Three lanes max: Faith, Identity, Art. No sub-lanes. No badges. Click toggles <code>aria-pressed</code> on the button and adds a filter class to the archive root. One lane active at a time; clicking the active lane resets to "all." Queued cells carry <code>aria-disabled="true"</code> + a descriptive <code>aria-label</code>.</p>
