            </header>
            <p>The issue opener. A two-column plate that splits a textured image (with latest-badge overlay) against an editorial body panel (eyebrow, title, deck, rail). Only plate variant that carries a deck. Used exactly once per issue.</p>
            <p class="s-note"><strong><code>.plate-row</code></strong> is an archive-density modifier. Drops a <code>.plate-secondary</code> card into a single-row layout so the title, deck, and meta sit inline. Use at the bottom of the archive for older entries where scale-parity with newer plates would be visual noise.</p>
